description:
Hello,

Our Salesforce-to-DataWarehouse sync integration has been throwing rate limit errors all morning. The sync runs every 15 minutes and each run is now failing. Here are the API responses we're getting:

Response 1 (08:00:03 UTC):
{"errorCode": "REQUEST_LIMIT_EXCEEDED", "message": "TotalRequests Limit exceeded.", "statusCode": 429, "retryAfter": 3600, "requestId": "4a8b-9c0d-1e2f-3a4b", "remainingRequests": 0, "dailyLimit": 100000, "used": 100000}

Response 2 (08:15:04 UTC):
{"errorCode": "REQUEST_LIMIT_EXCEEDED", "message": "TotalRequests Limit exceeded.", "statusCode": 429, "retryAfter": 3247, "requestId": "5b6c-7d8e-9f0a-1b2c", "remainingRequests": 0, "dailyLimit": 100000, "used": 100023}

Response 3 (08:30:02 UTC):
{"errorCode": "REQUEST_LIMIT_EXCEEDED", "message": "ConcurrentRequests Limit exceeded. Maximum concurrent requests allowed: 25", "statusCode": 429, "retryAfter": 30, "requestId": "6c7d-8e9f-0a1b-2c3d", "remainingRequests": 0, "concurrentLimit": 25, "active": 27}

Response 4 (08:45:01 UTC):
{"errorCode": "REQUEST_LIMIT_EXCEEDED", "message": "TotalRequests Limit exceeded.", "statusCode": 429, "retryAfter": 1853, "requestId": "7d8e-9f0a-1b2c-3d4e"}

We suspect the new marketing automation campaign that launched yesterday is consuming all our API calls. The daily limit is 100K requests and we've been hitting it by 8 AM. Before the campaign, we'd use about 60K/day total. We need to either increase our API limit or throttle the marketing sync.

— Fatima
